50|$|The Tamil people {{cultivated}} a {{wide range}} of crops such as rice, sugarcane, millets, black pepper, various grains, coconuts, beans, cotton, plantain, tamarind and sandalwood. Jackfruit, coconut, palm, areca and plantain trees were also known. <b>Systematic</b> <b>ploughing,</b> manuring, weeding, irrigation and crop protection was practiced for sustained agriculture. Water storage systems were designed during this period. Kallanai (1st-2nd century CE), a dam built on river Kaveri during this period, is considered {{to be one of the}} oldest water-regulation structures in the world still in use.|$|E

